                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d982">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">467.11 W 89/42: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the High
                        Commissioner at Constantinople</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bristol</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1923-12-20T18:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 20, 1923—6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>234. You are authorized to sign communication quoted in your telegram 332 of
                    December 19,<note n="44" xml:id="d982fn44">Not printed; the text submitted for
                        approval in telegram 332 was substantially the same as the translation of
                        the letter of Dec. 24 from Admiral Bristol to Adnan Bey, printed <ref
                            target="#pg_1190">p. 1190</ref>.</note> it being understood that Adnan
                        <pb facs="1313" n="1189" xml:id="pg_1189"/> Bey will address a communication
                    to you, <hi rend="italic">mutatis mutandis</hi>, like the one you address to
                    him.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
